TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF USE OF THE "LALIGA FANTASY" GAME
1.- OWNERSHIP AND PURPOSE
These terms and conditions regulate the terms of use (hereinafter, the "
Terms
") of the LALIGA Fantasy game in its app and web version (hereinafter, the "
Game"
) by the users of the same. Said Game is exclusively owned by LaLiga Group International, S.L., with Tax ID number B05421805 and registered office in Madrid, C/ Torrelaguna 60, 28043 (hereinafter, "
LALIGA
").
LALIGA is a company duly incorporated under the laws of Spain and is majority owned by the Liga Nacional de Fútbol Profesional. For more information about LALIGA please access the
Legal Notice
.
LALIGA provides the Game free of charge for those users who wish to play, consisting of a football manager where they can create virtual leagues to play with other users, the objective being to score as many points as possible. The score is obtained from the sum of the points obtained by each player lined up in each match day of the National First Division League Championship. Points are awarded to each player according to a series of criteria, including goals, yellow and red cards, among others.
IF THE USER HAS ANY COMMENTS, QUESTIONS OR REQUESTS PLEASE SEND AN EMAIL TO THE FOLLOWING ADDRESS: support@laligafantasy.zendesk.com
This Game has been developed to be used on mobile devices with iOS, Android OS, Windows Phone or other similar operating systems, and LALIGA can periodically update it.
2.- USER
The registration and creation of an account (hereinafter, the "
Account
") in order to use the Game automatically confers the status of user (hereinafter, "
User
") on the person who does so, and implies acceptance of and compliance with the Terms. In accordance with the above, the User is obliged to read these Terms, as well as any other conditions that regulate the use and enjoyment of the Game or its environment, before using or enjoying the Game. You may save these Terms or print them for future reference. LALIGA will also save the text of the entire contract and make it available to you on request.
The User is aware and voluntarily and expressly accepts that the use of the Game is in any case under his sole and exclusive responsibility.
Minimum age.
In order to register and use the Game you must be at least sixteen (16) years of age or have your parent's and/or legal guardian's permission to register and use the Game. Therefore, by accepting these Terms you warrant that you are at least sixteen (16) years of age or, if you are not, that you have parental consent to register for the Game and you accept full responsibility for this statement.
LALIGA may contact the User, at any time, to prove their real age by providing a photocopy of their National Identity Document or an equivalent document. In the event that the User does not provide the aforementioned documentation, LALIGA reserves the right to block the User's use of the Game.
Registration and single sign-on service (LALIGA Single Sign-On).
LALIGA has implemented a means of registration and single sign-on (LALIGA Single Sign-On) that allows the User to access an environment created by LALIGA (LALIGA Ecosystem) and integrated by several applications and websites, both of LALIGA and of the affiliated football clubs with which LALIGA has collaboration agreements, with the aim that the User can enjoy a series of advantages. Each user receives a unique identifier so that any selection or modification of preferences or deletion request made in one of the applications or websites that are part of the ecosystem will affect the rest of the LALIGA Ecosystem environment and the entities that comprise it.
Through LALIGA Single Sign-On, a unique "fan profile" is created in all the channels (assets) connected to LALIGA Ecosystem, which is shared by all the entities responsible for these assets (LALIGA apps and websites, affiliated clubs' apps and websites, etc.).
For more information on LALIGA Ecosystem please consult the following web link:
https://www.laliga.com/informacion-legal/laliga-ecosistema
.
3.- GENERAL CONDITIONS OF USE
3.1.- Registration: login and password
In order to be able to use and enjoy the Game, the User must register by providing the data required to validate the registration. In order to register, the instructions included in the registration form must be followed using the forms provided in the Registration option.
All the information provided by the User through the forms presented to access the functionalities of the Game for the aforementioned purposes or any other, must be truthful, and specifically, the User must be the owner of the e-mail address provided. To this effect, the User guarantees the authenticity of all the data that he/she provides, and that he/she will keep the information provided perfectly updated so that it corresponds, at all times, to the real situation of the User. In any case, the User will be solely responsible for any false or inaccurate statements made and for any damages caused to LALIGA or third parties as a result of the information provided.
When the User creates a User Account, he/she is given a user name and password (hereinafter referred to as "
Identifiers
") that he/she specifies, which will enable him/her to access his/her private Account. The Identifiers are personal and confidential. They can only be changed at the User's request or at LALIGA's initiative. For security purposes, the User undertakes to ensure that the password chosen to register for the Game is unique, i.e. that it is not used for any other application, e-mail account or similar. The assigned identifiers will be personal and non-transferable, and may not be transferred, even temporarily, to third parties. In this sense, the User undertakes to make diligent use of and to keep secret his or her assigned Identifiers, if applicable, to access the Game and/or the Content. In the event that the User knows or suspects the loss, theft or use of his/her password or confidential Identifiers by third parties, he/she must inform LALIGA as soon as possible.
The User will be able to select a preferred region to play (Spain or Global). This choice will imply differences in the content and functionalities of the game. For example, only in the game mode of the Spain region, users will be eligible to participate in the Sponsored Leagues and will have the possibility to watch DAZN's ‘partidazo’ every matchday. LALIGA therefore recommends users to choose the Spain region only if they reside in Spain as the prizes of the Competitions and Contests of the Sponsored Leagues can only be awarded to users in this territory.
The User shall be liable for the costs and damages caused by the access and use of the Game and/or the Content by any third party using User Identifiers for this purpose due to the non-diligent use or wilful loss of the User Identifiers.
3.2.- Other associated accounts
For certain aspects of the Game, you may be able to set up additional accounts that are dependent on your account ("associated account(s)"). The User agrees to be bound by these Terms for any associated accounts (including those of minors) that the User now has or subsequently creates, and that the User is responsible for all activity that occurs under his/her account and any associated account(s). You agree that LALIGA may take action against your account in response to activity on any of your associated accounts, including (i) limiting who may use your Game account or any associated account; (ii) limiting the number of devices from which you may access the Game; (iii) and/or deleting your Account or any associated account.
If you permit or authorise a minor to use an associated account:
The User declares that he/she is a parent or legal guardian of the minor;
The User agrees to supervise the use of the Game by minors who are permitted or authorised by the User to use the Game. The Game is not intended for use by children under the age of sixteen (16) without adult supervision;
If using an associated account, the User acknowledges that the Account holder has full control over its associated account. This control includes the right to: (i) terminate use and enjoyment of the Game; (ii) close or alter their associated account at any time; (iii) access or modify the Parental Controls for their associated account; and (iv) receive notifications from LALIGA. In some cases, this control also includes the ability to request and receive device usage information and Game services in relation to your associated account. Collect profile, usage and activity data relating to your associated account and send it to the account holder of the Game services.
3.3.- Incorrect use of the Game
The User undertakes to make appropriate use of the Game and the Content that can be accessed through it, and not to use it to engage in illegal activities or activities that are contrary to good faith and legal order; to disseminate Content or propaganda of a racist, xenophobic, pornographic or terrorist nature or that violate human rights; cause damage to the physical and computer systems of LALIGA or its suppliers, introduce or disseminate computer viruses or any other physical or computer systems that may cause the aforementioned damage.
3.4.- Provision of Content by the User: licensing and guarantees.
In the event that the functionality of the Game allows the provision of Content/s by the User (meaning the following: opinions, observations, comments, graphic material, photographs, links, questions, suggestions, information, videos, audio and other material that the User sends to the Game or communicates using the Game), the User is free to make the same available, providing LALIGA with the information that may be required in relation to the origin and ownership of the Content and the procedure by which the User has obtained it. This information must be truthful and verifiable in the event that LALIGA so requires.
LALIGA shall decide freely and without any obligation on its part which Content is to be made available to the public via the Game. In the event that LALIGA opens up the possibility of accessing Content made available through the Game by Users, these Users declare that they know and accept that, once made available to other Users of the Game, the Content will be available to third parties throughout the world, and therefore expressly exempt LALIGA from liability for any claims for this reason.
3.4.1.- Rights granted by the User under licence.
All Content communicated by the User through the Game cannot be considered confidential and/or private. The User acknowledges and accepts that LALIGA only acts as a passive channel for the distribution of any Content generated by the User, and does not assume any responsibility and is not liable to the User or any third party for the Content or the accuracy of the Content generated.
In this sense, the User expressly acknowledges that by making available to LALIGA different Contents in the Game, these have been obtained, produced and/or acquired directly by the User, in such a way that he/she holds all the necessary rights over them, with sufficient legitimacy to transfer them to LALIGA under the terms and conditions established in this document. Thus, by virtue of this document and by means of the aforementioned act of making available, the User will be granting:
(I).- In favour of LALIGA, a worldwide, non-exclusive, free, sub-licensable and transferable licence to make any use of the Content, including its commercial exploitation, as well as for advertising and non-commercial uses, to reproduce, distribute, publicly communicate and transform the Content, to make derivative works of the Content, all in relation to the provision of the services of the Game and the operation of the Game and the activity of LALIGA, including, without limitation, for the purposes of promotion and redistribution of all or part of the Game (and its derivative works) in any format and through any communication channel;
(II) To each user of the Game, a worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free licence to access the Content through the Game, and to use, reproduce, distribute, make derivative works of display and perform such Content to the extent permitted by the functionality of the Game and subject to these Terms.
The above licences granted by the User in respect of the Content shall be cancelled when the User removes or deletes the User Content from the Game.
The above licences granted by the User with respect to the User Content are perpetual and irrevocable, without prejudice to their ownership rights, the ownership of which shall at all times correspond to the User, as stipulated in the previous section.
3.4.2.- Guarantees
In the event that a User makes, if the functionalities of the Game so permit, Content available to other Users of the Game, this implies that such User guarantees that:
a) That the Content does not imply or contain defamation or slander of any person, company or association, that it does not infringe the regulations for the protection of honour, personal privacy and self-image in force in Spain at the time of submitting the Content, and that nothing in it infringes intellectual property rights, industrial property, or any other right belonging to third parties.
b) That in order to make this transfer of rights, it has the authorisations of the persons appearing in the Content.
c) The User represents and warrants that he/she holds (and will continue to hold while using the Game services) all licences and all rights, consents and permissions necessary to enable LALIGA to use his/her Content for the purposes of providing the Game service and for any other purpose in the manner contemplated by the Game and these Terms.
d) The User undertakes not to publish or upload any Content that contains material that is illegal for the User to possess in his/her country of residence, or whose use or possession is illegal for LALIGA in connection with the provision of the Game services.
e) The User undertakes that the Content that the User provides to the Game will not contain material subject to intellectual property rights of third parties or material subject to other industrial property rights of third parties (including rights of exclusivity or publicity), unless the legal holder of such rights has granted a licence or formal authorisation, or is otherwise legally authorised, to publish the material in question and to grant LALIGA the aforementioned licence.
f) Upon becoming aware of any breach of these Terms, LALIGA reserves the right (but shall not be obliged) to decide whether Content complies with the Content requirements set out in these Terms, and may remove such Content and/or terminate the access of any User to upload Content in breach of these Terms at any time, without notice and at its sole discretion.
LALIGA will pursue the breach of the previous conditions as well as any improper use of the Content presented in the Game, exercising all civil and criminal actions that may correspond to them by law. If the User sees Content in our Game that he/she considers to be illegal, harmful or offensive, he/she is kindly requested to inform LALIGA at the following e-mail address: support@laligafantasy.zendesk.com.
3.5.- Other Contents
With the exception of the Content provided to the Game by the User, all other Content in the Game will be owned or licensed to LALIGA and will be subject to copyright, trademark rights and other intellectual and industrial property rights of LALIGA or LALIGA's licensors. All trademarks and service marks of other third parties present in the Content not uploaded or published by the User shall be trademarks and service marks of their respective owners.
Such Content may not be downloaded, copied, reproduced, distributed, transmitted, broadcast, displayed, sold, licensed or exploited for any purpose without the prior written consent of LALIGA, or LALIGA's licensors, if applicable. LALIGA and its licensors reserve all rights not expressly granted with respect to its Content.
3.6.- Advertising
The User knows and accepts that advertising may appear in the Game and that, therefore, he/she will be able to access advertising either from LALIGA and/or from third party companies or professionals that contract with LALIGA.
Likewise, it is possible that the app shop through which the User downloads the Game may allow the User to pay an economic amount so that advertising does not appear in the Game. In this sense, LALIGA disclaims any responsibility for the relationship that is entered into between the User and the owner of the app shop so that advertising does not appear in the Game. In the event that the User is interested in exercising their right to terminate the contract signed with the app shop, they will have to comply with the cancellation policy of the app shop in question.
3.7.- Exemption from liability
LALIGA shall not be liable for any damages caused by the improper use of the Game by Users. Any act that contravenes the applicable legislation will be the responsibility of the User who carries them out.
In this sense and within the limits established in the applicable regulations, LALIGA will not be liable for any infringements made by any User of the Game that may affect any other User of the same, or third parties, including those that refer to intellectual property rights, industrial property, confidential information and/or any other similar right. Likewise, they will not be liable for the infringements of a User to the personal privacy, honour and/or image of another User or a third party, which will be the exclusive responsibility of the infringer, whether they are statements made in forums, opinions of the user or audio-visual materials provided by the user, in the event that such functionalities exist.
The User accepts responsibility and accepts the consequences derived from the infringement of these rules, and undertakes to hold LALIGA harmless from any claim for this reason.
Any liability that LALIGA may be charged with for any damage or loss for any of the above in a judicial or extrajudicial proceeding, by a Court, Tribunal or competent administrative Public Body, shall be repeated against the User including all amounts that LALIGA has had to pay and bear, including consequential damage and loss of profit, and any costs or charges that it may have had to face, including taxes, fees, lawyers' fees, solicitors' fees, arbitration and any other.
3.8.- Virtual Currencies
The Game may include virtual currencies ("
Virtual Currencies
") or items or services for use with the Game ("
Virtual Items
"). In order to use or enjoy Virtual Coins and/or Virtual Items in the Game, the User may be required to obtain a certain level or progress to a certain point. In this regard, the User agrees that, once acquired, Virtual Coins and Virtual Items have no monetary value and cannot be exchanged for real money, real items or real services by LALIGA or anyone else. The User agrees that the Virtual Coins and/or Virtual Items are not transferable to anyone else, and that the User will not transfer or attempt to transfer the Virtual Coins or Virtual Items to anyone else.
3.9.- Premium Access with Tokens
The Game may include the option to purchase one-time payment tokens that allow the User to access new functionalities or enhancements within it. Tokens are a one-time payment and not a subscription. The price of tokens is set at the time of purchase and is not subject to change for that specific purchase.
LALIGA reserves the right to modify the price of tokens for future purchases due to changes in market conditions, significant increases in acquisition or service provision costs, or in the case of variations in VAT or any other similar tax. Price changes will be reflected directly in the Application and will be effective for purchases made after the price change date. No prior notification to users will be required for token price changes, as these do not involve recurring payments or subscriptions.
3.10.- Subscriptions
The Game includes paid subscriptions that allow the User to enjoy LALIGA Fantasy without advertising. By paying a monthly fee, the User will be able to use the Game without having to watch advertisements.
Subscriptions are open to users of legal age who reside in Spain. To do so, it will be necessary to have a credit or debit card with a Spanish bank or linked to the iTunes account.
Payment will be made through the account associated with the User's device, either App Store or Google Play. It is necessary to have a credit/debit card associated with the account.
The subscription to the ad-free Game will be charged once a month, on or around the day on which the User subscribes. If the billing date is scheduled for a day that does not exist in every month (e.g. the 31st), it will be charged on the last day of that month.
The subscription will be renewed automatically. In case the user does not want the subscription to be renewed automatically, the user will have to cancel the subscription at least 24 hours before the end of the current period. The renewal will be charged on the same day the subscription starts.
The User may cancel their subscription and continue to enjoy LALIGA Fantasy with advertisements by accessing their account settings on their device, accessing the purchased subscription and requesting cancellation.
To request a refund of a subscription, it will depend on:
If the User made a subscription request from an iOS device, the User must access the URL: https://support.apple.com/es-es/HT204084 and request a refund. You must first confirm whether the purchased product is eligible for a refund under Apple's refund policies.
If the User made a subscription request from an ANDROID device and you wish to withdraw, you can request a refund within the first 48 hours by accessing your account settings. You can find more information at:
https://support.google.com/googleplay/workflow/9813244?p=refundAWF&visit_id=637768946016484052-2789740922&rd=1
