The Game may be available to the User through LALIGA's own media and services as well as on various portals, services, platforms, environments and third-party tools.
These Terms complement any other general terms and conditions that may regulate the website from which the Game can be accessed, or any service, procedure, mechanism, platform, environment or means that may be necessary for the use of the Game, and prevail over these texts in the event of any discrepancy.
Some Game services accessible to Users may be subject to special conditions, regulations and instructions which, where applicable, substitute, complete and/or modify the present Terms and which will be understood to have been accepted by the User when the corresponding service is provided.
It is not permitted to carry out techniques or actions within the Game that are fraudulent or contrary to the proper use and normal operation of the Game in any of its game formats (e.g. LALIGA Fantasy or sponsored leagues):
Any mechanism likely to be out of the ordinary that leads to accumulating all the money or the best players in a single user.
Any option that involves out-of-market sales and unrealistic prices.
5.- LINKS TO THIRD PARTIES
For the convenience of the User and for the purpose of enhancing the use of the Game, links to websites owned and controlled by third parties may be provided from time to time.
These links take you outside the service and are beyond the control of LALIGA. The sites to which the User may link have their own independent terms and conditions, as well as their own privacy policy, and LALIGA is not responsible and cannot be held liable for the Content or activities of these sites. Therefore, your visit or access to these sites is at your own risk.
In particular, LALIGA will not be responsible for the technical availability, nor for the Contents, nor for the damages that the User may suffer as a consequence of the consultation or use of the Contents offered through a web page that the User accesses from the Game. In particular, the User may find on these associated pages surveys or forms in which he/she is asked to provide personal or other information, for different reasons or purposes. The User is free to accept or not these offers, but if he/she does so, he/she will establish a direct relationship with the third party in question, and it is possible that LALIGA has no relationship with the third party other than the establishment of a link or access from the LALIGA Game. In this case, this website will be governed by its own data protection rules and general conditions (which will normally be different to those of the Game), which the User must consult and, if applicable, accept.
6.- SPONSORED LEAGUES
Sponsored Leagues are virtual leagues that may be managed either by LALIGA or by LALIGA's commercial partners ("
Partners
"), therefore LALIGA shall not be liable for the Content, nor for any damages that the User may suffer as a result of consulting or using the Content offered through a League sponsored by a Partner that the User accesses from the Game.
If a User decides to register to participate in one of the Sponsored Leagues offered by LALIGA in its Game, he/she will be asked to fill in specific complementary forms in each case, having to fill in at least those fields that are indicated as obligatory for the achievement of the aims and purposes for which that specific Sponsored League is intended. Once the form has been correctly completed, a confirmation e-mail will be sent to the address indicated by the User. By registering in the Sponsored League, the User expressly authorises LALIGA to transfer his/her personal data to the Partner responsible for said Sponsored League, whose name will be indicated in the legal bases accepted by the User, so that the Partner can provide the service requested by the User, as well as for those other purposes indicated in the aforementioned legal bases.
It is the User's responsibility that all information provided during participation in these Sponsored Leagues is accurate and up to date.
The obligatory data are specified in the form itself, and your refusal to provide them will mean that you will not be able to register as a participant in the Sponsored Leagues.
6.1.- Mahou Sponsored League
The Mahou Sponsored League is a league that is not managed by LALIGA but by MAHOU, S.A. Consequently, LALIGA shall not be held responsible for the Contents, nor for any damages that the User may suffer as a result of consulting or using the Contents offered through the Sponsored League that the User accesses from the Game.
6.2.- Dazn Sponsored League
The League Sponsored by Dazn, is a league that is not managed by LALIGA but by DAZN SPAIN, S.L., therefore, LALIGA will not be responsible for the Contents, nor for the damages that the User could suffer as a consequence of the consultation or the use of the Contents offered through the Sponsored League to which the User accesses from the Game.
6.3.- Competitions and Contests
Competitions in which you enter within a Sponsored League or those run directly by LALIGA or by a Partner through specific promotions may be governed by supplemental terms and conditions, but the following general rules apply to all competitions unless otherwise specified in the supplemental terms and conditions.
Submissions and Participation
Submission of Content by the User to participate in the contests is subject to all of the provisions of these Terms regarding submission of User Generated Content. We may disqualify submissions that are late, not sent to the proper address, incomplete or in corrupt files, lost, illegible or invalid, or for which the necessary parental or guardian consent has not been provided. Participation in contests is limited to one submission per person and the use of agents or third parties or the use of multiple identities is not permitted. The use of automatic submission or voting mechanisms and other similar programmes is prohibited; all submissions (or votes) made by such methods will be disqualified.
We reserve the right to modify, suspend, cancel or terminate a contest, to extend or resume the contest entry deadline or to disqualify any participant or submission at any time and without prior notice. We will do so if we cannot guarantee that the contest will be conducted fairly or correctly for technical or legal reasons, or for other justifiable reasons not attributable to us, or if we suspect that any person has manipulated submissions or results, provided false information, or acted unethically. In the event that we cancel or terminate a competition, prizes may be awarded in any manner we deem fair and appropriate in accordance with the local law governing the competition. We will inform entrants of these circumstances and any changes as soon as possible.
Eligibility requirements
To enter a contest, you must be a registered User of one of the Sponsored Leagues running a contest or competition and have an active account with current contact information. No purchase is necessary to enter a contest and making a purchase will not increase your chances of winning. Competitions are not open to members of LALIGA and the Partner managing the Sponsored League (or their immediate family members, these are first degree) or anyone else who is connected with the competition by virtue of their profession. We reserve the right to request proof of identity or to verify the conditions of participation of potential winning submissions, as well as to deliver any prize in person to the winner.
Responsibility
In the event that LALIGA organises a prize draw and/or competition through the Game, the prize draw and/or competition will not be sponsored, endorsed or administered by, or in any way associated with, any app shop or social network. The User dissociates himself/herself completely from the owner of the app shop or social network and is aware that he/she is providing his/her personal information and data to LALIGA and not to the app shop or social network.
Awards
There will be no cash or alternative prizes, however, LALIGA Partner reserves the right to substitute a prize with a similar prize of equal or greater value. Winners may not transfer or sell their prizes. Only the number of prizes indicated for the competition will be available and all prizes will be awarded provided that a sufficient number of valid entries have been received and prizes are validly claimed before the date indicated in the competition, after which date no alternative winners will be selected and no unclaimed prizes will be awarded. Unless otherwise stated in the prize description prior to entry into the competition, winners are responsible for all costs and expenses incurred in claiming their prize. All taxes are the sole responsibility of the winner, although we reserve the right to withhold applicable taxes and the winner agrees to complete the appropriate tax forms.
By accepting a prize, the prize winner consents to participate in reasonable publicity in connection with the contest and grants us the unconditional right to use his/her name, city or town and state, province or country, likeness, prize information and statements about the contest for advertising or promotional purposes in accordance with applicable law, all without obtaining his/her permission or offering additional compensation. As a condition of receiving a prize, winners (or their parents or guardians) may be required to sign and submit an affidavit stating that they are eligible to enter, that they release us from liability, and that they assign to us the rights necessary to conduct the publicity.
